\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. A. helvetica} (L.) All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem. }{\b 1}: 91 (1785) ({\i A. imbricata} Lam.). Densely caespitose perennial; stems regularly branched, forming deep, dense, more or less hemispherical cushions. Leaves 2-6(-7·5) × 0·5-1·5 mm, lanceolate, oblong or spathulate, more or less densely pubescent with simple hairs, densely imbricate, persistent after withering and forming columnar shoots. Flowers solitary. Pedicels very short or absent; involucral bracts absent. Calyx 2-3·5 mm, pubescent. Corolla 4-6 mm in diameter, white with a yellow throat. Seeds 1-1·5 mm. 2n = 40.{\i  Mountain rocks; calcicole. • Alps; ?Pyrenees.} Au Ga Ge He It.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. A. vandellii} (Turra) Chiov.,{\i  Nuovo Gior. Bot. Ital.} nov. ser.,{\b  26}: 27 (1919). ({\i A. imbricata} auct., non Lam., {\i A. multiflora} (Vandelli) Moretti, non Lam.). Like {\b 13} but leaves linear-lanceolate, densely whitish-tomentose with stellate hairs; pedicels 1-8(-12) mm. 2n = 40.{\i  Mountain rocks; calcifuge. •  Alps, Pyrenees, Sierra Nevada.} Au Ga He Hs It.
\par 

