\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. A. hausmannii} Leybold, {\i Flora} ({\i Regensb}.) {\b 35}: 401 (1852). Caespitose perennial; branches shortly capitate, rosettes few, not forming a cushion. Leaves 5-10 × 1-1·5 mm, linear-lanceolate, densely pubescent with stellate or forked hairs, not persistent after withering. Flowers solitary. Pedicels 1-12 mm, pubescent. Calyx 3-4 mm, pubescent. Corolla 4-5 mm in diameter, pink with a yellow throat. Seeds 1-1·5 mm. 2n = 40.{\i  Rocks and screes above} 1900{\i  m; calcicole. • E. Alps, westwards to} 10° 50'{\i  E.} Au Ge It Ju.
